# ExamForge — AI Exam Prep Platform (India)

## Project Context
Monorepo: Next.js 15 + Fastify 5 + PostgreSQL 17 + AWS (App Runner + RDS + ElastiCache).
Target exams: BPharm Asst Prof, NEET, GPAT, UPSC, Kerala PSC, GATE.

## TypeScript Rules
- Strict mode, no `any`, no `as` type assertions unless justified with comment
- Named exports, ES modules only, 2-space indent
- Explicit return types on all exported functions
- Use `satisfies` operator over `as` for type narrowing
- Prefer `const` assertions for literal types

## React / Next.js Rules
- Server Components by default, add `"use client"` only when needed
- Use `useActionState` for form handling (React 19)
- Data fetching: TanStack Query for client, server actions for mutations
- No `useEffect` for data fetching — use TanStack Query or RSC
- Tailwind v4 utility classes only, no custom CSS unless absolutely necessary
- shadcn/ui components — never build custom UI primitives

## API Rules
- tRPC routers in `apps/api/src/routers/`
- Zod validation on every input
- Return `{ success, data?, error? }` pattern
- Auth middleware: verify session on all protected routes
- Rate limit AI-related endpoints (10 req/min per user)

## Error Handling
- Use early returns (guard clauses)
- Custom `AppError` class with code, message, statusCode
- Never swallow errors silently — log with structured JSON
- AI calls: retry 3x with exponential backoff, then queue for later
